.TH "ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits" 9 "ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits \- Calculates traffic class credits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" ixgbe_dcb_calculate_tc_credits
.BI "(struct ixgbe_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "struct ixgbe_dcb_config *dcb_config "  ","
.BI "int max_frame "  ","
.BI "u8 direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to hardware structure
.IP "dcb_config" 12
Struct containing DCB settings
.IP "max_frame" 12
Maximum frame size
.IP "direction" 12
Configuring either Tx or Rx
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function calculates the credits allocated to each traffic class.
It should be called only after the rules are checked by
\fBixgbe_dcb_check_config\fP.
